<br>
Something else not mentioned in this thread ... Luclin mobs and their higher AC.<br>
<br>
Before a recent patch it wasn't really much of an issue, since 90 percent of the mobs I was facing were dark blue cons either in a small group or solo. 2hb seemed the better choice for me merely on the riposte issue.<br>
<br>
Lately I've been fighting a lot tougher mobs due to the XP changes. And I find crushing every 40 seconds for pitiful damage kind of not helping my cause. Heh.<br>
<br>
Tstaff parses very well and is an amazing weapon at any level of the game. So keep it. Even IF it becomes just a situational weapon, you'll be glad you had it during those situations.<br>
<br>
But it's not the holy grail of monk weapons everyone makes it out to be.<br>
<br>
It's just another tool for you to use while playing the game.<br>
<br>
